ORIENTATION SEPT 8TH
- Introduced the course structure, objectives, and expectations. went over the course outline, departmental fees, lab access, and available resources.
- reviewed HTML and CSS to refresh our understanding of basic web layout and styling. Then, we moved into a JavaScript + DOM review

READY SEPT 15TH - SEPT 22
- introduced to Python foundations and learned how to access and use web APIs. The focus was on understanding how Python can handle data communication between servers and clients.
- worked with the World Air Quality Index API, practicing how to send API requests, interpret responses, and document the retrieved data.

STEADY SEPT 29TH - OCT 20TH
- Understanding how requests and responses are exchanged. We also studied client-server protocols, the Fetch API, and the basics of Flask
- practiced serving web pages using Flask and handled POST and GET requests to save and retrieve data between clients and servers.

GO NOV 3 - NOV 17
- set up Flask application, create and modify HTML templates, and incorporate JavaScript to enable interaction. processing POST requests from the user via Fetch, saving data to a file, and finally displaying.
